  <fr:li>Let <fr:tex>\square</fr:tex> be a suitable <fr:em>internal cube category</fr:em> in <fr:tex>\mathbf {PER} { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathbb {A} \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex>\mathbb {O}</fr:tex> be an internal well-founded order in the same.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Then the category of internal presheaves of assemblies <fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \left  [ { \mathopen {} \left ( \square \times \mathbb {O} \right ) \mathclose {}} ^{ \mathsf {op} } , \mathbf {Asm} { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathbb {A} \right ) \mathclose {}} \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is expected to form a model of <fr:strong>iGHoTT</fr:strong>{}.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>Impredicative <fr:strong>HoTT</fr:strong> via cubical assemblies due to <fr:link
